        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1926",
        "content": "When I stole into the parlor Anson Kirkpatrick, Marshall Field's man, was at the piano, playing airs from a musical comedy then running in Chicago. He was a dapper little Irishman, very vain, homely as a monkey, with friends everywhere, and a sweetheart in every port, like a sailor.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
